FT  21 JUN 93 / Licensing deal for Leyland supplier
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KEVIN DONE, Motor Industry Correspondent
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
MOTOR PANELS, a subsidiary of the specialist engineering company Mayflower,
has reached a licensing agreement with Leyland Trucks Manufacturing to
market the Ley-land cab range outside west Europe.
The Mayflower subsidiary is one of the most important suppliers to the newly
formed Leyland Trucks Manufacturing, which was acquired as a management
buy-out from the receiver two weeks ago following the financial collapse
earlier this year of Daf, the Dutch commercial vehicle maker, and Leyland
Daf its UK subsidiary.
Motor Panels supplies the cabs for the present truck ranges produced at the
plant in Leyland, Lancashire, including the 45-series of light trucks.
Under the exclusive licensing agreement Motor Panels will be able to produce
the cabs for customers outside west Europe and for other specific Leyland
Truck Manufacturing markets.
In parallel with the formation of Leyland Trucks, Motor Panels has signed a
new five-year contract with the company to supply cabs with a value
estimated initially at about Pounds 20m over the life of the deal.
