FT  21 JUN 93 / Two bombs defused in Egypt
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By AP
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   CAIRO
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
POLICE in Egypt defused two bombs yesterday, including one in the Cairo
suburb where a bomb blast killed seven people last week, news reports said,
AP writes from Cairo.
The state-run Middle East News Agency said a package containing a bomb was
left in front of a shop on a busy street at Aswan, a main tourist town in
the south.
A resident noticed the package and called police, the agency said. The bomb
contained nails, a timer and gunpowder, an interior ministry official told
the MENA.
In the Cairo suburb of Shubra, police found another bomb, cordoned off the
area and defused it, the newspaper al-Ahram reported early today.
