<HEADLINE>
FT  19 JUN 93 / Finance and the Family: Unit trusts win tax concession - At
a Glance
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
The unit trust industry scored a success this week after intensive lobbying.
Stephen Dorrell, financial secretary to the treasury, committed the
government to introduce legislation in the next Finance Bill to allow unit
trusts to pay income gross to non-UK residents. This would allow onshore UK
trusts to compete with other collective funds, based in Luxembourg and
Dublin. The government also decided to remove an anomaly, relating to the
change in advance corporation tax in this year's Budget, which might have
led to the sale of substantial unit trust holdings by UK life companies.
